<h2>Article-title #1</h2>
<small>2011-20-13</small>
<p>Finding the right coding bootcamp can be overwhelming. There are so many options out there and so many factors to consider. With the Internet overflowing with coding bootcamps, the key is to know exactly what you are looking for. Important factors to keep in mind are tuition fees, duration of the course or courses, and topics covered. You should also consider the success rate of graduates and where alumni are now employed.</p>

<p>We took on the daunting task of choosing the best online bootcamps to narrow it down for you. These are the top ten best online coding bootcamps of 2020.</p>

<p>The Flatiron School is a New York-based educational organization that teaches software engineering, computer programming, data science, UX/UI design, and cybersecurity analytics. The school offers both online and in-person education. Flatiron campuses can be found in NYC, Brooklyn, Washington DC, London, Houston, Atlanta, Austin, Seattle, Chicago, and Denver. The school prepares students for positions in the industry, such as software engineers, data scientists, and cybersecurity engineers. Additionally, on-campus students boast a 93% employment rate while the average salary for online graduates is $76,000. The school also offers free introductory courses if you are looking to test the waters first. The application process consists of a written application and an interview. You will need to demonstrate proficiency in certain skills before entering the program.</p>


<p>Thinkful was founded on the premise of providing accessible tech training to all. The school offers a variety of programs, including part-time, full-time, online, and self-paced. The curriculum focuses on UI/UX Design, Data Science, Data Analytics, Web Development, Digital Marketing, Product Management, Engineering Immersion, and Full Stack Development. Students have a personal mentor, a career coach to help them enter the workforce, a support network composed of peers, and an academic success manager. Following graduation, 88% of students find full-time employment.</p>

<p>App Academy is considered of the most respected programs in the tech industry. The school is a full-time software development bootcamp with in-person and online programs, including a bootcamp prep course. Graduates go on to work for tech giants, including Google, Apple, and Twitter, to name a few. One of the most alluring aspects of this program is that if you don’t gain employment after graduation, you don’t have to pay a dime.</p>

<p>Founded in 2011 in New York, General Assembly was originally a community of start-ups and entrepreneurs. The tech bootcamp now boasts over 20 campuses worldwide, including Boston, Chicago, and London. They offer programs in web and mobile development, digital marketing, and product management, among others. A variety of financing options are available, such as scholarships, payment plans, and employee sponsorships. Hiring partners for General Assembly include Microsoft and Conde Nast.</p>

